cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses adversarial training and generative adversarial networks (GANs) in the context of deep learning, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the robustness of the discriminator under adversarial attacks, which is a topic of interest in the sub-field of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for joint optimization of generator and discriminator, which is a topic of interest in the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.NE, in that order.
